Statistical analysis
Statistical analyses were carried out with the SPSS Sta-
tistics 23.0 (SPSS Inc., Chicago, IL, USA). For each com-
pound, six solutions were prepared and analyzed by
GC–MS. The statistical analysis was obtained comparing
the analyte/anisole area ratios in the solutions with the
corresponding concentrations. A value of P correspond
ent to 0.011 was considered significant.
